Sublime Text 3 is now supported

---------------------------------------------------------------------

I'm still using Sublime Text 2 while reviewing C# syntax. Instead of using MonoDevelop in Linux or Xamarin Studio in Windows, I created a Sublime Text 2 plugin that will compile and debug C# source code.

Install Mono if you want to use this plugin. In Windows, Mono installation directory should be added to the environment variable Path.

You can watch the demo at http://youtu.be/BQ2C0iTk36o
